NOTE FOR UPSTREAM SUBMISSION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When submitting to the kernel tree:

1. Rename excalibur.c → drivers/platform/x86/excalibur-wmi.c
2. Add the Kconfig stanza above to drivers/platform/x86/Kconfig
3. Add `obj-$(CONFIG_EXCALIBUR_WMI) += excalibur-wmi.o` to
   drivers/platform/x86/Makefile
4. Copy the MAINTAINERS block above (without this NOTE section) into
   the kernel's top-level MAINTAINERS file, in alphabetical order by
   subsystem name (between "EXCEED CARD DRIVER" and "EXFAT FILE SYSTEM").
5. Add a Documentation/admin-guide/laptops/excalibur-wmi.rst file
   (can be derived from the project README).
6. Send patches to linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org and
   platform-driver-x86@vger.kernel.org, CC the maintainer above.

Mailing list archive: https://lore.kernel.org/platform-driver-x86/
Patch submission guide: Documentation/process/submitting-patches.rst
